transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes, hi. My name is Nicolas Gladius. I recently ordered a prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: And I want to make sure that I'm not on auto retail. I want to make sure that I actually order when I...

Speaker 1: What's your zip code?

Speaker 2: 11542.

Speaker 1: And what was your name again?

Speaker 2: Last name is Gladius. K-L-A-D-I-A-S.

Speaker 1: Okay. One second.

Speaker 2: To Viola Drive?

Speaker 1: Yep, yep.

Speaker 2: Okay. So if you don't have a refill date set, sir, in the future, you don't have to accept it on that day,

Speaker 1: but if you don't even have a date set, you wouldn't be able to order down the road.

Speaker 2: So I can do that for you, but this would be your one and only order.

Speaker 1: Yes. For now, yes, because I'm going to Europe, so...

Speaker 2: That's fine. That's all fine, sir. There's just no for now. This was one and done now.

Speaker 1: So we're all set. Your prescription has been canceled because we covered the cost of the doctor's visit,

Speaker 2: and now we're not going to pay for that cost again since you canceled right away.

Speaker 1: So we're all set.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Account's closed. Goodbye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
